<paragraph id="8C7E79D95AD43A4C6FF708389FB11DD5" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">
<taxonomicName id="7EF693C53419CD32DF98EA22BD9A3ACA" LSID="89AD46E9-6094-5704-BF99-46C415F99A66" authority="(Forel, 1892)" authorityName="Mayr" authorityYear="1861" baseAuthorityName="Forel" baseAuthorityYear="1892" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Temnothorax" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Temnothorax bulgaricus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="bulgaricus">Temnothorax bulgaricus (Forel, 1892)</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="5607FD13C5B3857847A2E3809396BB1D" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="820DAFE675ED76274BA82688FC74A61C" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">Distribution</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F37B9D41CCBD43F9ABB8D1603426697A" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">
New records: South Pirin Mt., Kalimantsi vill., 10.05.-01.06.2002, pitfall traps, 1 w., leg. M. Langourov; Struma Valley, Kamenitsa vill., 31.05-23.06.2002, tree traps, 1 w., leg. M. Langourov; East Rhodopes, Strazhets vill., 03.05.2009, 2 w., leg. ALG; Sakar Mt., Radovets vill., 30.04.2011, sweeping, 3 w., leg. I. Gjonov; East Rhodopes, Meden buk vill., 09.04.2013, 1 w., leg. ALG. Detailed occurrence data: 
<bibRefCitation id="B2EB265D0425B131E0E566A1C71A68C3" author="Lapeva-Gjonova, A." journalOrPublisher="Biodiversity Data Journal" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" refId="B7741022" refString="Lapeva-Gjonova, A., Borowiec, L., 2022. New and little-known ant species (Hymenoptera, Formicidae) from Bulgaria. In: Biodiversity Data Journal. Occurrence dataset." title="New and little-known ant species (Hymenoptera, Formicidae) from Bulgaria" volumeTitle="Biodiversity Data Journal. Occurrence dataset." year="2022">Lapeva-Gjonova and Borowiec (2022)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="E527EA24FFCD125E6D92C146C9EC7464" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" type="notes">
<paragraph id="725B320A258D449908FD823A7DE0391A" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">Notes</paragraph>
<paragraph id="38B1FF138BB9BB2740834245B9F488DE" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">
After the description of 
<taxonomicName id="C3D561274E39A33DB5F7A0AB0E43651F" genus="T." lsidName="T. bulgaricus" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" rank="species" species="bulgaricus">
<emphasis id="CF4871644BA39149A94437DC05B63439" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">T. bulgaricus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Bulgaria (
<bibRefCitation id="DC87E95D3A348CC81DC8D09F323276CA" author="Forel, A." journalOrPublisher="Verhandlungen der Zoologisch-Botanischen Gesellschaft in Wien" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" pagination="305 - 318" refId="B7727072" refString="Forel, A., 1892. Die Ameisenfauna Bulgariens. (Nebst biologischen Beobachtungen). Verhandlungen der Zoologisch-Botanischen Gesellschaft in Wien 42: 305 - 318" title="Die Ameisenfauna Bulgariens. (Nebst biologischen Beobachtungen)" volume="42" year="1892">Forel 1892</bibRefCitation>
), it has been reported from a number of places in the southern Balkans and Turkey. It was found in several thermophilous sites (Sliven, Zemen Gorge, Petrich, Asenovgrad, Obzor) in Bulgaria (
<bibRefCitation id="AD93676B19504BE28E25747D69ADB49C" author="Atanassov, N." journalOrPublisher="Bulgarian Academy of Sciences, Sofia" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" refId="B7725616" refString="Atanassov, N., Dlussky, G. M., 1992. Fauna Bulgarica. 22. Hymenoptera, Formicidae. Bulgarian Academy of Sciences, Sofia" title="Fauna Bulgarica. 22. Hymenoptera, Formicidae" year="1992">Atanassov and Dlussky 1992</bibRefCitation>
). Here we provide additional findings as South Pirin Mt., East Rhodopes Mt. and Sakar Mt. are hitherto unknown distribution regions.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
